Apply now Apply now save-icon Job details Salary $75,000 - $90,000 a year Job Type Full-time Senior Data Analyst Physician’s Weekly, a leading medical news service and custom healthcare publishing company for doctors and their staff, is seeking a Senior Data Analyst to join our Basking Ridge, NJ based data team. In this critical position, the Senior Data Analyst will handle post-sale fulfilment both for our print and digital contracts. We are looking for a competent individual who can coordinate with multiple teams to manage our print inventory to accurately allocate available inventory for signed contracts and report the remaining availability. In addition, you must prepare the email lists necessary to fulfill contracts related to our client’s email campaigns. Your job is important since the efficient handling of the company’s products and services is critical for the attainment of business goals. The role requires a technically savvy individual who is curious about the larger strategic picture and who thinks creatively on how best to answer critical business questions with the data available. This is a high-paced role and requires the ability to stay focused while handling multiple projects under tight deadlines. Essential Functions Gather data from various data sets using Alteryx and other ETL tools. Manage print inventory availability for all clients by locking in print wallboard locations per contract as they come in, then reporting the updated inventory numbers. Author reports on our sold vs unsold wallboard locations on a rolling basis to provide insights on current and projected trends to be shared with upper management. Generate email lists for upcoming client digital campaigns and apply analytics capabilities to monitor their behavior to determine user habits across our digital platforms. Adapt and improve inventory management processes as necessary. Use tools and techniques to visualize data in easy-to-understand formats such as spreadsheets and Power BI. Communicate with stakeholders to understand data content and prioritize business requirements. Autonomy to operate with a limited level of direct supervision by showcasing the ability to exercise independent judgment. Requirements/Qualifications Bachelor’s degree in data related field of study or 5+ years’ experience in data analytics intensive role. Minimum 3-5 years’ experience in a data analytics function with core daily responsibilities in with databases such as SQL Server, Oracle, MS Access, etc. Strong SQL skills are required, including an ability to write and troubleshoot SQL queries from scratch. Knowledge of relevant relational databases & understanding of data sources, data organization and storage. Minimum 2-3 years’ experience using data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or Qlik Sense. Highly analytical with ability to extract and analyze large amounts of data and draw actionable insights and recommendations. Ability to synthesize complicated data into actionable messages for those who are ‘not technical’. Strong analytical skills and basic knowledge of statistical methodologies and data analysis techniques. Exposure to data manipulation using Alteryx or other ETL tools a plus. Experience with Python or other programming languages a plus Understanding of the healthcare industry and physician databases is ideal. Attention to detail and ownership of tasks. Strong interpersonal skills and clear verbal and written communication skills. Critical thinking and time management skills a must. Interested? Please email jobs@physweekly.com, attaching a current resume and a cover letter explaining why you would be a good fit for the job. Please include the title of the position being applied for and your desired salary requirements. Learn more about Physician’s Weekly by visiting us at www.physiciansweekly.com . To this end, in partnership with the New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene (DOHMH), FPHNYC incubates innovative public health initiatives implemented by DOHMH to advance community health throughout the city. It facilitates partnerships, often new and unconventional, between government and the private sector to develop, test, and launch new initiatives. These collaborations speed the execution of demonstration projects, effect expansion of successful pilot programs, and support rapid implementation to meet the public health needs of individuals, families, and communities across New York City. PROGRAM OVERVIEW DOHMH COVID-19 Vaccination Plan- Round 4 Supplemental Gotham Center, LIC The New York City (NYC) Department of Health and Mental Hygiene (DOHMH) Bureau of Immunization (BOI) Citywide Immunization Registry (CIR) is a central record-keeping system established by DOHMH to track the immunization status of individual children and adults, monitor immunization levels in the population in a timely manner, and implement publicly purchased vaccine ordering, management, and accountability. The CIR is accessible to licensed health care providers, parents and agencies authorized by the DOHMH for the retrieval of immunization records for the purpose of ensuring that children and adults receive all required immunizations and are, thereby, protected from vaccine-preventable diseases. POSITION OVERVIEW The Data Analyst will conduct analyses of CIR data and produce reports including graphs, and maps related to immunization uptake and coverage to support Bureau of Immunization initiatives. Participate in the development of methods for measuring and improving vaccination coverage rates in the NYC population. Work closely with internal teams and CIR vendor to plan, develop, implement, and evaluate protocols and research related to CIR data quality assurance. Coordinate data analyses and research projects using CIR data with other units within BOI, DOHMH, and in collaboration with CDC. Prepare reports and presentations using CIR data for internal, local, and national meetings and conferences. Participate in the development of manuscripts for publication. Performs other duties as needed to meet BOI objectives.
